= Appendix Languages

Tips and tricks on language use.

== English
<sec:english>

- There is a distinction between "allows" and "enables".

== Native German Speakers
<sec:native-german-speakers>

- In English, there is rarely a comma before "that, that".
    If you feel the urge to add one, you are likely mistaken.
- English generally avoids the excessive use of uppercase letters.



